<p><b>Gin rummy</b> (or <b>Gin</b> for short) is a simple and popular two-player <a href="/wiki/Card_game" title="Card game">card game</a> created by <a href="/wiki/Elwood_T._Baker" title="Elwood T. Baker" class="mw-redirect">Elwood T. Baker</a> and his son, <a href="/wiki/C._Graham_Baker" title="C. Graham Baker" class="mw-redirect">C. Graham Baker</a>, in 1909.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> Gin, which evolved from 18th-century Whiskey Poker (according to <a href="/wiki/John_Scarne" title="John Scarne">John Scarne</a>),<sup class="noprint Template-Fact"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources&#160;since September 2008" style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed">citation needed</a></i>]</span></sup> was created with the intention of being faster than standard <a href="/wiki/Rummy" title="Rummy">rummy</a>, but not as spontaneous as knock rummy.</p>
